## PART 1: WHAT THE AIs AGREED ON (High-Confidence Consensus)

These items appeared consistently across all sources and are treated as canonical:

### The Two-Phase System

Every AI independently identified the same architecture:

**PHASE A — THE CAGE (Moves 1–10)**
The exact structure to build in every line:

- Pawns: e4 + d3 + c3
- Bishop: Bc4 → Bb3 (preserve on the a2-g8 diagonal — never trade for a knight without a structural fight)
- King: Castled by move 6–7
- h3: Non-negotiable. Stops Bg4 pins. Enables safe Be3.
- Rook: Re1 (supports e4, eyes e-file)
- Knight: Nbd2 → Nf1 (loaded and ready)

**PHASE B — THE ASSASSIN (Moves 11+)**
The strike sequence — identical across all lines:

```
Nf1 → Ng3 → Nf5
Bb3 (hold the diagonal)
Be3 or Bg5 (activate second bishop)
Qe2 (centralize, support e4)
Re1 → Re3 → Rg3/Rh3 (rook lift)
d4 break ONLY when Ng3 is ready
Pressure target sequence: f7 → g7 → h7
```

